'''Lehmon Colbert''' (born April 14, 1988) is an American professional [[basketball]] player who currently plays for the [[UCC Demons]] of the Irish [[Superleague (Ireland)|Superleague]]. He played [[college basketball]] at [[Jacksonville University]].

==High school career==
Colbert attended Crawford County High School in [[Roberta, Georgia]]. As a senior, he averaged 25 points, 13 rebounds, six assists, four steals and three blocks per game. He was also named to the second team all-state in Class 2A as a junior, and the first team all-state in Class 2A as a senior.<ref name=bio>{{cite web | url=http://www.judolphins.com/mbasketball/roster/103/2217/ | title=2009-10 Men's Basketball <U+2013> Lehmon Colbert | work=JUDolphins.com | accessdate=May 26, 2014}}</ref>

==College career==
In his freshman season at [[Jacksonville Dolphins men's basketball|Jacksonville]], Colbert was named to the 2007 A-Sun All-Freshman team. In 29 games (28 starts), he averaged 11.7 points, 5.2 rebounds and 1.1 assists per game.<ref name="bio" /><ref name=stats>{{cite web | url=http://www.sports-reference.com/cbb/players/lehmon-colbert-1.html | title=Lehmon Colbert Stats | work=Sports-Reference.com | accessdate=May 26, 2014}}</ref>

In his sophomore season, he had his most productive college season, scoring in double figures 24 times while going for 20 points or more three times. In 31 games (all starts), he averaged 13.1 points, 6.3 rebounds an 2.6 assists per game.<ref name="bio" /><ref name="stats" />

In his junior season, he became the 26th member of the school<U+2019>s 1,000-point club. He scored in double figures 22 times while going for 20 points or more two times. In 32 games (all starts), he averaged 11.8 points, 6.2 rebounds and 1.7 assists per game.<ref name="bio" /><ref name="stats" />

In his senior season, he was named to the 2010 All-A-Sun second team. In 28 games, he averaged 12.1 points, 6.8 rebounds and 1.5 assists in 28.5 minutes per game.<ref name="stats" />

==Professional career==
Colbert went undrafted in the [[2010 NBA draft]]. In August 2010, he signed a one-year deal with the [[Plymouth Raiders]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/other_sports/basketball/8948029.stm | title=Lehmon Colbert completes Plymouth Raiders squad | work=BBC.co.uk | date=August 27, 2010 | accessdate=May 26, 2014}}</ref>

In May 2011, Colbert signed a one-year contract extension with the Plymouth Raiders.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.bbc.com/sport/0/basketball/13548597 | title=Lehmon Colbert signs new deal with Plymouth Raiders | work=BBC.com | date=May 26, 2011 | accessdate=May 26, 2014}}</ref>

In May 2013, Colbert signed with Le<U+00F1>adores de Madera of Mexico for the rest of the 2013 season.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.facebook.com/photo.php?fbid=482247371856111 | title=El nuevo refuerzo lehmon colbert!! | work=Facebook.com | date=May 31, 2013 | accessdate=May 26, 2014 | language=Spanish}}</ref>

In September 2013, Colbert signed with the [[UCC Demons]] for the 2013<U+2013>14 [[Superleague (Ireland)|Superleague]] season.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.bluedemonsbc.com/index.php?module=Pagesetter&func=viewpub&tid=1&pid=1038 | title=C&S UCC Demons Announce The Signing Of Lehmon Colbert | work=BlueDemonsBC.com | date=September 20, 2013 | accessdate=May 26, 2014}}</ref>

==Personal==
Colbert is the son of Irene Colbert.<ref name="bio" />

